==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[absorptio]]'', from ''[[absorbere]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/əbˈzɔ:p.ʃən/}}, {{SAMPA|/@b"zO:p.S@n/}}
*{{audio|en-us-absorption.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or process of [[absorbing]] or [[sucking]] in anything.
# The act or process of being [[absorbed]] and made to [[disappear]].
#:''the '''absorption''' of bodies in a [[whirlpool]]''
#:''the '''absorption''' of a smaller tribe into a larger
# {{context|chemistry|physics}} An [[imbibing]] or [[reception]] by [[molecular]] or chemical action.
#:''the '''absorption''' of light, heat, electricity, etc.''
# {{physiology}} In living organisms, the process by which the materials of growth and [[nutrition]] are absorbed and conveyed to the [[tissue]]s and [[organ]]s.
# Entire [[engrossment]] or occupation of the mind.
#:'''''absorption''' in some employment''

